{
  "video_id": "GKCoAtO0zzM",
  "title": "Sensors and Actuators Overview | Intel Software",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 499.0,
      "end_time": 2130.0,
      "text": "Hi, I'm Daniel Holmlund."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2130.0,
      "end_time": 4740.0,
      "text": "In this video we're going to\ndo a quick overview of sensors"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 4740.0,
      "end_time": 6720.0,
      "text": "and actuators and\ntake a closer look"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 6720.0,
      "end_time": 9360.0,
      "text": "at what's provided inside\nthe Grove IoT Sensor Kit."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 12270.0,
      "end_time": 14100.0,
      "text": "A sensor is defined\nas a device that"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 14100.0,
      "end_time": 17310.0,
      "text": "can record a measurement about\nits physical environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 17310.0,
      "end_time": 18900.0,
      "text": "This measurement can\nthen be converted"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 18900.0,
      "end_time": 22470.0,
      "text": "into an electrical signal that\ncan be read by an Arduino 101"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 22470.0,
      "end_time": 24750.0,
      "text": "and is forwarded to a\ngateway or to the cloud"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 24750.0,
      "end_time": 26340.0,
      "text": "for additional processing."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 26340.0,
      "end_time": 28500.0,
      "text": "The electrical signal\nconnects to the Arduino"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 28500.0,
      "end_time": 31290.0,
      "text": "with a couple of different\ntypes of connectors."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 31290.0,
      "end_time": 33630.0,
      "text": "Sensors encode their\ndata in different ways"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 33630.0,
      "end_time": 36660.0,
      "text": "in order to best represent the\ndata to the computer system"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 36660.0,
      "end_time": 37860.0,
      "text": "they talk to."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 37860.0,
      "end_time": 40140.0,
      "text": "The first type is\na digital sensor."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 40140.0,
      "end_time": 43590.0,
      "text": "The Grove Button and the\nSwitch are both examples that"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 43590.0,
      "end_time": 45840.0,
      "text": "send simple digital signals."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 45840.0,
      "end_time": 47700.0,
      "text": "They're either on\nor they're off."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 47700.0,
      "end_time": 50100.0,
      "text": "The second type is\na digital actuator."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 50100.0,
      "end_time": 53940.0,
      "text": "The Grove Buzzer and Grove LTD\nare both digital actuators."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 53940.0,
      "end_time": 55410.0,
      "text": "That is they can\nchange their state"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 55410.0,
      "end_time": 58500.0,
      "text": "and perform an action depending\non whether on or off signal"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 58500.0,
      "end_time": 59610.0,
      "text": "is sent to them."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 59610.0,
      "end_time": 62070.0,
      "text": "The Buzzer will make a noise\nand the LCD will light up"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 62070.0,
      "end_time": 63660.0,
      "text": "when a high signal was sent."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 63660.0,
      "end_time": 66810.0,
      "text": "They both deactivate\nwhen the signal is low."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 66810.0,
      "end_time": 70170.0,
      "text": "On the Arduino 101, a\nvoltage of 3.3 volts"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 70170.0,
      "end_time": 73530.0,
      "text": "is considered on or high\nand a voltage of zero"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 73530.0,
      "end_time": 75510.0,
      "text": "is considered off or low."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 75510.0,
      "end_time": 77850.0,
      "text": "The Grove Temperature\nSensor, Rotary Angle Sensor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 77850.0,
      "end_time": 81000.0,
      "text": "and Light Sensor are\nexamples of analog sensors."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 81000.0,
      "end_time": 84330.0,
      "text": "This means that they receive a\nvoltage somewhere between zero"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 84330.0,
      "end_time": 86280.0,
      "text": "and 3.3 volts."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 86280.0,
      "end_time": 89130.0,
      "text": "The Arduino 101 has an\nanalog to digital converter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 89130.0,
      "end_time": 91950.0,
      "text": "or ADC, which takes the\nsignal and converts it"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 91950.0,
      "end_time": 96480.0,
      "text": "into a 10-bit number, which is\na number between zero and 1023."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 96480.0,
      "end_time": 100440.0,
      "text": "So, for example, if a sensor is\nsending a voltage of 1.65 volts"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 100440.0,
      "end_time": 102990.0,
      "text": "to the Arduino, the\nconverter would read this"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 102990.0,
      "end_time": 105870.0,
      "text": "as approximately 512."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 105870.0,
      "end_time": 108510.0,
      "text": "Lastly, the LCD\nscreen is an actuator"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 108510.0,
      "end_time": 110460.0,
      "text": "that is capable of\ndisplaying a message"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 110460.0,
      "end_time": 113580.0,
      "text": "and illuminating its backlight\nto any eight-bit color."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 113580.0,
      "end_time": 116160.0,
      "text": "It's not a simple\ndigital or analog device."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 116160.0,
      "end_time": 120680.0,
      "text": "It uses a serial communication\nprotocol called I squared C."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 120680.0,
      "end_time": 122820.0,
      "text": "The I squared C\nprotocol allows devices"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 122820.0,
      "end_time": 125760.0,
      "text": "to communicate their\ninternal timing clocks"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 125760.0,
      "end_time": 128880.0,
      "text": "and then communicate data\nusing a serial protocol."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 128880.0,
      "end_time": 131039.0,
      "text": "I squared C devices\ncan be chained,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 131038.99999999999,
      "end_time": 133650.0,
      "text": "meaning that multiple\ndevices can be attached."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 133650.0,
      "end_time": 135270.0,
      "text": "And together, these\ndevices are said"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 135270.0,
      "end_time": 138240.0,
      "text": "to be on an I squared C bus."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 138240.0,
      "end_time": 140280.0,
      "text": "Each device is given\nan address that can"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 140280.0,
      "end_time": 143190.0,
      "text": "be communicated to on that bus."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 143190.0,
      "end_time": 145410.0,
      "text": "In the video on\nMRAA and UPM, we'll"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 145410.0,
      "end_time": 147090.0,
      "text": "see how to use a\nhigher level software"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 147090.0,
      "end_time": 149400.0,
      "text": "library to abstract\naway these details"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 149400.0,
      "end_time": 152100.0,
      "text": "and to give an easy-to-use\ninterface to more"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 152100.0,
      "end_time": 153900.0,
      "text": "complicated devices."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 153900.0,
      "end_time": 155620.0,
      "text": "Thank you very\nmuch for watching."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 155620.0,
      "end_time": 158370.0,
      "text": "Remember to like this video and\nsubscribe to the Intel software"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 158370.0,
      "end_time": 159510.0,
      "text": "YouTube channel."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 159510.0,
      "end_time": 161550.0,
      "text": "Follow the links below\nto get more information"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 161550.0,
      "end_time": 165590.0,
      "text": "on what we discussed and\nlook us up on Facebook."
    }
  ]
}